        <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-20">
            <div class="content-box" style="background-color: #ffffff; padding: 15px;">
                <h5>
                    <span style="color: #333333; font-size: 20px;"><strong>About the Thesis Workflow</strong></span>
                </h5>
                <p>With the Thesis Workflow, students can easily publish their Master Thesis to the UvA Library within Canvas. The workflow consists of a few modules within each course in which, according to our settings, students have to carefully read and follow one-by-one in order to complete it. By using this structure, students are well-informed about the decisions they have to make, such as which creative commons licenses they can choose of. By following the workflow module-by-module, students can hand in their thesis according to their wishes and decisions.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid-row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-7">
                <img style="width: 100%; margin-top: 10px;" src="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/8175/files/2758416/download?wrap=1" alt="Canvas view teachers" data-api-endpoint="https://canvas.uva.nl/api/v1/courses/8175/files/2758416" data-api-returntype="File" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-4">
                <h2>
                    <span style="color: #333333; font-size: 20px;"><strong>Workflow checklist</strong></span>
                </h2>
                <div class="alert alert-success" style="width: 100%; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                    <p>You are welcome to <strong>edit due dates</strong> of the assignments.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="alert alert-success" style="width: 100%; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                    <p>Please <strong>keep the Modules menu open and visible</strong>. This way, students can start off with the first assignment of the workflow and click &ldquo;next&rdquo; to follow the process. Try to <strong>close the Assignments menu</strong> to prevent confusion for students.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="alert" style="width: 100%; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                    <p>Please <strong>do not create any alternate/substitute assignments</strong>. Students will have to submit their thesis in the workflow assignment inbox that we imported to your course.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="alert" style="width: 100%; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                    <p>Please <strong>do not change the titles</strong> of the assignments and modules, otherwise it will not be possible to upload a thesis to the UvA Library.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="alert" style="width: 100%; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                    <p>Noticed the strange titles above each assignment (in the Assignments menu) such as <strong>&ldquo;reporting.id.concept&rdquo;</strong>? These <strong>titles should not be edited</strong> as well.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="content-box" style="background-color: #ffffff;">
    <div class="grid-row">
        <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-20">
            <div class="styleguide-section__grid-demo-element">
                <div class="content-box pad-box-mini border border-trbl border-round" style="background-color: #fcfcfc; padding: 20px;">
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">Dear teachers,</p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">
                        <span lang="EN-US">We hope this email finds you well - we want to inform you about the The Thesis Workflow in your course. This is an UvA wide method for the Final Thesis Submission to the UvA Library.
                            <br />ICTO Social Sciences implemented the flow in Semester 2 of 2020 and this year we're reaching out to you with a reminder of how it works and how to use it (and how not to).&nbsp;
                            <br />
                        </span>
                    </p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">&nbsp;</p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">
                        <span lang="EN-US"><strong>Quick overview</strong>
                            <br />To gain a quick overview of Thesis Workflow, check out<span>&nbsp;</span>
                            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLdqh3iVhzW1SWyn7loiUIaAr3KNy4rkb4" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                                <span>these videos</span>
                            </a>.
                        </span>
                    </p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">&nbsp;</p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing"><strong>
                            <span lang="EN-US">The basics
                                <br />
                            </span>
                        </strong>
                        <span lang="EN-US">To ensure students upload their thesis correctly, they have to take four these which are known as the <strong>Thesis Workflow</strong>:</span>
                    </p>
                    <ol>
                        <li class="x_MsoNoSpacing">
                            <span lang="EN-US">Students start with submitting the thesis title for their diploma supplement</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="x_MsoNoSpacing">
                            <span lang="EN-US">Then there are one or two surveys/quizzes, depending on whether a student wants to publish their thesis in the UvA Library or not</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="x_MsoNoSpacing">
                            <span lang="EN-US">After that they can upload their thesis in PDF</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="x_MsoNoSpacing">
                            <span lang="EN-US">Finally there's a webpage to notify them that they've successfully uploaded their thesis.</span>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">
                        <span lang="EN-US">To see what it looks like in terms of Canvas assignments, quizzes and pages, check out the <strong>screenshots below</strong>.</span>
                    </p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">&nbsp;</p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing"><strong>
                            <span lang="EN-US">Three important notes:</span>
                        </strong></p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">
                        <span lang="EN-US">a. When the theses are uploaded, do <strong>not use Canvas&rsquo;s Gradebook</strong> but grade them as usual. Use the regular evaluation form for grading (&ldquo;beoordelingsformulier&rdquo;) and use SpeedGrader to find out what the<span>&nbsp;</span>
                            <a class="instructure_file_link inline_disabled" href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/8175/pages/urkund-homepage" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-api-endpoint="https://canvas.uva.nl/api/v1/courses/8175/pages/urkund-homepage" data-api-returntype="Page">
                                <span>plagiarism score</span>
                            </a>
                            <span>&nbsp;</span>is.
                        </span>
                    </p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">
                        <span lang="EN-US">b. <strong>Email <a class="instructure_file_link inline_disabled" href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/8175/pages/uva-thesis-workflow-information#menu3" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-api-endpoint="https://canvas.uva.nl/api/v1/courses/8175/pages/uva-thesis-workflow-information%23menu3" data-api-returntype="Page">this text</a> to your students</strong> (or use an announcement) to inform students of the changes.</span>
                    </p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing"><strong>
                            <span lang="EN-US">c. It's imperative that you do not change any settings</span>
                        </strong>
                        <span lang="EN-US">. Here's the&nbsp;<a class="instructure_file_link inline_disabled" href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/8175/pages/uva-thesis-workflow-information#menu2" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-api-endpoint="https://canvas.uva.nl/api/v1/courses/8175/pages/uva-thesis-workflow-information%23menu2" data-api-returntype="Page">detailed explanation</a>, below is the rundown:</span>
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <span>Don't use 'Syllabus' or 'Assignments' as your homepage.
                                    <br />
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        <span>The Assignments and Syllabus menus have to be invisible for students. </span>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        <span>Work with 'Modules' (Because 'Assignments' aren't visible for students) and </span>
                                        <span>add a new assignments, pages or quizzes. </span>
                                        <span>
                                            <a class="Hyperlink  BCX0 SCXW95220523" href="https://community.canvaslms.com/docs/DOC-26329-how-do-i-add-course-content-as-module-items" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                                                <span class="TextRun Underlined  BCX0 SCXW95220523" lang="EN-US" data-contrast="none">
                                                    <span class="NormalTextRun  BCX0 SCXW95220523" data-ccp-charstyle="Hyperlink">Here's how.</span>
                                                </span>
                                            </a>
                                        </span>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <span>Don't change the Assignment codes. The workflow only works if the assignments related to the Thesis Workflow remain </span>
                                <span>published</span>
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        <span>All assignments within an assignment group starting with: reporting.id[...]</span>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        <span>All assignments within an assignment group starting with: publication.id[...] </span>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <span>Don't turn off the Mastery Paths.&nbsp; They are turned on in the Settings menu.</span>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">&nbsp;</p>
                    <p class="x_MsoNoSpacing">
                        <span lang="EN-US">All the best,</span>
